#=======================================================================================================
# Java programs that deal with deriving an i2b2 ontology from metadata held within an Onyx export file
#=======================================================================================================

 Usage: OnyxVariables2Metadata {Parameters}       
        Parameters:
         -input=path-to-onyx-export-directory
         -output=path-to-working-directory
        Notes:
         (1) Parameter triggers can be shortened to the first letter; ie: -i,-o.
         (2) The input parameter is the only mandatory one.
         (3) If the output path parameter is omitted, output is directed to standard out.
         (4) If the output path parameter is provided, the working directory must not exist.
         
         
 Usage: MetadataRefiner {Parameters}       
	    Parameters:
	     -input=path-to-onyx-metadata-directory
	     -config=path-to-xml-config-file
	     -refine=path-to-main-refine-directory
	     -enum=path-to-main-refine-enum-directory
	     -name=refined-metadata-file-name
	    Notes:
	     (1) Parameter triggers can be shortened to the first letter; ie: -i, -c, -r,-e,-n.
	     (2) All parameters are mandatory.
	     (3) The input path must exist.
	     (4) The config file must exist (See test data for examples)
	     (5) The refine and enum paths must not exist.
         (6) Suggested refined metadata file name: Refined-Metadata.xml.